        "src": "gdelt",
        "exit_case": "PPA was signed September 20 \u2014 the specific named deal-signing catalyst has already occurred and stocks already popped.",
        "resolved": true,
        "assessment": "Microsoft's 20-year PPA with Constellation Energy to restart Three Mile Island was signed and publicly announced on September 20, 2024 \u2014 the exact entry date. The Motley Fool confirms CEG, NuScale, Nano Nuclear, and Oklo all popped on the news that day. The specific catalyst as stated \u2014 'Microsoft signs 20-yr PPA' \u2014 is a named deal-closing event, and it has now closed. Downstream events such as NRC license reinstatement and the actual restart of TMI Unit 1 (expected ~2028) are real and concrete, but they are NEW catalysts not entered on. The edge of positioning ahead of this specific announcement is gone. The instructions are unambiguous: 'named deal closed' = catalyst_resolved. Exit the position; do not conflate the broader nuclear renaissance theme with the specific catalyst entered on.",
        "exit_advice": "Exit CEG. The stated catalyst is 'Microsoft signs 20-yr PPA' \u2014 a named deal closing \u2014 and it closed on entry day (Sept 20). The immediate pop is already in. Per the exit rule, a named deal signed/closed resolves the catalyst regardless of downstream events (NRC reinstatement, actual TMI restart) that were not the entered catalyst."
      }
    ],
    "CCJ": [
