        "resolved": true,
        "assessment": "The fixed catalyst (Amazon signing named SMR deals with X Energy and Energy Northwest) resolved on or around October 16, 2024 \u2014 two days before entry. By entry date the event is already a closed, publicly-announced discrete signing, covered wall-to-wall by IBD ('Amazon Goes Nuclear; Stock of the Day Cameco Explodes'), Benzinga, Motley Fool, Forbes, and Yahoo Finance. The CCJ pop has already occurred. Coverage is mainstream-saturated on day one of this position. No concrete, scheduled follow-on catalyst is identified in the news \u2014 there is no named NRC filing date, no construction-start milestone, no additional signed agreements pending; only the ambient AI-energy demand theme persists, which is speculative and generic, not a datable catalyst. Both exit conditions are met simultaneously: (1) the catalyst arc is complete (the deal is signed, the press has processed it), and (2) coverage has turned fully mainstream with retail frenzy and sell-side chasing nuclear stocks broadly. Catalyst_resolved = true forces thesis_live = false. The early-mover window was compressed to zero before a position could even be established.",
        "exit_advice": "Exit CCJ immediately. The specific catalyst \u2014 the named deal signing \u2014 occurred before entry date and is now saturating mainstream financial press. No early-mover edge remains."
      }
